An unlikely friendship ‚ù§Ô∏è
Video by: @eddieandboomer -
*Disclaimer: Please DO NOT approach or touch wildlife and do not encourage pets to engage with wildlife. Your or your pet‚Äôs scent can be a hazard to them and attract unwanted predators. This video happened by chance, please do not try to recreate this video by any means as we want to encourage all of our followers to respect and admire wildlife from a distance. ‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
STORY: Eddie & Boomer met a new baby deer friend this morning. A note about the mama deer - Until fawns are strong enough to keep up with their mom's during the day, the mama deer hide the fawn in tall grasses, in a meadow, etc. while mama goes off to feed. Mama comes back for the fawn later. It's best to leave the fawn alone. Older deer fawn wander a little. This sweet fawn wandered into our yard & our dogs stumbled upon it. Eddie & Boomer let him go on his way (over to the horse pasture). We stayed out of it and let mama and fawn reunite on their own, as they normally do. We looked around this morning and no sign of the fawn, so we trust all is well. :)
